Result: false  
Justification:  
The condition C11 requires that for every minimal semantic basis of the claim, there exists at least one P-type argument whose justification contains that basis. Here, the claim is "Jamari is a good footballer." The minimal semantic basis for this claim, derived from the given universal statement, is that Jamari must have good speed or good agility (or both). However, none of the P-type arguments include this required basis in their justifications—they only mention quick reflexes, strategic skills, and performing well, which do not entail good speed or good agility. Therefore, C11 is not satisfied.